description: First attested 1432, from Middle French putatif, from Latin putātīvus (“supposed, purported”), from putātus (“thought”), from putō (“I think, I consider, I reckon”).

adjectives.description: putative (comparative more putative, superlative most putative)

entries.meaning: (derogatory) Commonly believed or deemed to be the case; accepted by supposition rather than as a result of proof.
